{"word":"ἀκτέος","slug":"ἀκτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀκτέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:ἄγω'><el>ἄγω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one must lead</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>εἰρήνην ἀκτέον</el> <i>one must keep</i> peace, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>one must go</i> or <i>march</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}